Bridgewater Associates, LP

1 Glendinning Place 
Westport CT 06880 United States
Phone: +1 203-___-____
Fax: +1 203-___-____
https://www.bridgewater.com





88
Managers




158
IT employees




$65.5MEST.
IT Budget




Bridgewater Associates is a hedge fund that serves institutional investors. It was founded in 1975 by Ray Dalio and has approximately $125 billion in assets under management. This is an employee-owned company.
The Information Technology department works closely with operational and financial groups to support business operations. The technology team has its own IT operations group that manages strategic plans, portfolios, talent management, and other business operational procedures solely for IT.

The IT… MoreThe Information Technology department works closely with operational and financial groups to support business operations. The technology team has its own IT operations group that manages strategic plans, portfolios, talent management, and other business operational procedures solely for IT.

The IT department is divided into the following core teams: IT finance, information security, project management office, IT procurement, and infrastructure services. 

The department is specifically concentrating on building out the company's disaster recovery and backup engineering plan. Currently, the company uses a variety of different storage products, though Bridgewater acts mainly as an EMC shop in this respect. Staff members within this group are also focused on supporting the company's voice systems and building out a Linux infrastructure.

The application portfolio group is emphasizing support of the company's SharePoint solution. This group is a vital part of the department, supporting BI software by Cognos and SAS, as well as digital content software by Adobe.

Intelligence indicates that all new business must be physically mailed to the company.  





